****************************************************************
            TO CREATE A VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
****************************************************************

It is raccomended to create a virtual environment inside the dir "python_2D_sim"

In LINUX - OSX (MAC)

This is to install the virtualenv command:

> pip install virtualenv 

Then, to create the virtual environment named "venv" type:

> virtualenv venv

or

> python -m venv venv

To activate the virtual environment "venv" type:

> source venv/bin/activate

Inside "venv" (that is, when "venv" is activated) you have 
to install the required packages (see below)

To deactivate "venv" type:

> deactivate



****************************************************************
            TO INSTALL REQUIRED MODULES
****************************************************************

In LINUX - OSX (MAC)

> pip install numpy
> pip install pyqt6
> pip install PyOpenGL PyOpenGL_accelerate

In WINDOWS

> py -m pip install numpy
> py -m pip install pyqt6
> py -m pip install PyOpenGL PyOpenGL_accelerate

****************************************************************
                          TO RUN
****************************************************************
To Run the simulator from terminal:
> python3 main.py -s (INT) -f json_files/(file_name) -v true
Es: >python3 main.py -s 26265 -f jason_files/experiment_1.json -v true

To run the simulator without the graphics:
> python3 main.py -s (INT) -f json_files/(file_name)
Es: >python3 main.py -s 26265 -f jason_files/experiment_1.json

By adding & at the and, the simulator runs in background:
> python3 main.py -s (INT) -f json_files/(file_name) &
Es: >python3 main.py -s 26265 -f jason_files/experiment_1.json &

To know more about the command line arguments:
> python3 main.py -h

The -s (INT) can be omitted, and the seed number wil be taken from the json file
